            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": ", but turning that around is in some ways even more interesting.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "src": "__GHOST_URL__/content/images/2021/02/modern-F1-liveries-classic-cars.jpg",
        "width": 1920,
        "height": 1080,
        "caption": "image credit: YouTube"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Usually, people would be nervous about making such modifications to timeless classic cars such as these. That, and the cars are rare to come by, so the only sensible thing is to use a virtual format to experiment with the aesthetics. While some people would automatically run to Photoshop and start flexing their digital painting skills, these guys had a less-conventional idea.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "As you’ll see in the video, they turned on their PlayStation and fired up Gran Turismo. In the game, er driving simulator, you can apply custom liveries to cars, which you might have done before. But did you think to apply modern F1 liveries to classic cars? Well, you don’t have to since these guys already did it. So sit back and enjoy the show.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
